    <div class="smallsublist">
        <header>
            <h3>Films in the French Poetic Comedies: Jacques Tati:</h3>
        </header>
        
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxb mo0711"
                     data-href="/on/film/791">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/ea/e6/eae6d72383e98dca01cff9b4b3f2a7bc.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/72/d9/72d9b3269a88ab4db2bf231eb3113374.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">10</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/791">Jacques Tati I: Jour De Fete + French Wine And Conversation! (1949)</a></h1>

                <h2>10 Jul 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>Telling the story of an inept and easily-distracted French mailman, who interrupts his duties to converse with the local inhabitants, this film contains wine drinking and a lot of cycling! </p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/791">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

            </section>
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxa mo0711"
                     data-href="/on/film/790">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/f8/8b/f88b8c40e8d520ee663293a296e29ffa.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/2e/0b/2e0be75d0d0904632570ef78f1685fd6.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">14</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/790">Jacques Tati Ii: Les Vacances De Monsieur Hulot + French Wine And Conversation! (1953)</a></h1>

                <h2>14 Jul 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>Introducing the shy, complex, and elegantly maladroit Monsieur Hulot, this film “might contain the greatest collection of sight gags ever committed to celluloid” (The Independent). </p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/790">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

            </section>
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxb mo0711"
                     data-href="/on/film/789">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/d3/da/d3da587a5b6908d940e85c176aaff389.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/06/7f/067fcdb132df501cc745d9e9291c1b8e.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">28</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/789">Jacques Tati Iii: Mon Oncle (1958)</a></h1>

                <h2>28 Jul 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>Winner of the Oscar and the New York Film Critics Award for Best Foreign Film, and of a Special Prize at the prestigious Cannes Film Festival, this incredible film is centred around Monsieur Hulot, adored uncle of young Gerard, who struggles to fit into ultra-mechanised and geometric new demands of Modernity.</p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/789">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

            </section>
            <section class="row dmod clickable boxa mo0711"
                     data-href="/on/film/792">
                <div class="pull-left">
                    
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/a7/35/a735dc1dc88f98991f1121c058db8991.jpg"/>
                        
                        
                            <img class="img-responsive visible-xs" alt="" src="/media/cache/ca/14/ca143b45f7d63f92d3b6947ce3377552.jpg"/>
                        
                    
                </div>

                <h1 class="domdom">31</h1>

                <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/792">Jacques Tati Iv: Play Time (1967)</a></h1>

                <h2>31 Jul 2011, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                <p>Seen as Tati’s most daring film, an enormous set was built for the film, known as “Tativille”, for which Tati participated financially, and which stretched the production of the film to 3 years. </p>

                <p class="viewlink"><a href="/on/film/792">Read More &raquo;</a></p>

            </section>
